UNDIAGNOSED ILLNESS - USA: (FLORIDA) TEENAGERS, SPIKED DRINK, POISONING SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
**********************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 26 Apr 2022
Source: Local 10 [edited]
https://www.local10.com/news/local/2022/04/26/911-calls-released-after-6-students-fall-ill-at-military-ball-in-davie/


Local 10 News has obtained the 911 calls made after 6 teenagers fell ill earlier this month [April 2022] while attending a military ball in Davie.

"And one of them is really having some convulsions and going into shock," one caller said.

"OK, so you said they took some type of drugs?" the dispatcher asked.

"We think they got some kind of drugs from their drink," the caller said.

The incident occurred the night of 14 Apr [2022] at the Signature Grand venue at 6900 W. State Rd 84.

Davie police spokeswoman Sarah Andeara said while the substance the students took is unknown at this time, authorities believe it was "an over-the-counter legal substance."

We are told this was a combined military ball for members of J-ROTC at Northeast High School and another school.

"The water at one of our tables, it had drugs in them. People started putting drugs in them," student [EC] said. "We don't know exactly who or how many people did it, but for the kids who drank it -- the Northeast kids who drank water -- they got high and everything."

Some of the students who were there say some of their friends took a turn for the worse, and it happened quickly.

"One moment we are in the ballroom dancing, and the next, one person starts feeling dizzy and throwing up real bad," student [LT] said.

Police spokesperson Andeara said the incident was isolated to the 6 students who were transported to the hospital. No foul play is suspected, she said.

[Byline: Amanda Batchelor]

